title: Henry VI: A Good, Simple and Innocent Man (Penguin Monarchs)
description:
Henry VI: A Good, Simple and Innocent Man (Penguin Monarchs) - James Ross [epub]

Henry VI (reigned 1422-1461 and 1470-1471) succeeded to the throne at the age of only nine months and had a turbulent reign: he inherited a war with France and, in time, found himself at war with his own nobles.

James Ross surveys this eventful life, including Henry's deposition at the hands of Edward IV and his eventual return to the throne
